Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for the full module map. Follow these rules when changing game code.

# Dependency rules

1. **`engine.ts` is the hub** — imports domain modules and render helpers; domain modules must not import `engine.ts`.
2. **Render modules are pure drawing** — receive `CanvasRenderingContext2D` and read-only game state; do not mutate `GameData` or advance simulation.
3. **`app/` is outside the game domain** — input collection stays next to `App.tsx` so `src/game/` stays testable without React.
4. **Data modules stay side-effect free** — `aircraft.ts`, `weapons.ts`, `chapters.ts`, `modes.ts` export config and pure helpers only.

# Runtime flow

```text
App.tsx (RAF)
  ├─ inputRef  ← keyboard / pointer handlers
  ├─ update() or updateBackground()  ← engine.ts
  └─ render()  ← engine.ts
        ├─ chapters / hazards / enemies (domain draw)
        └─ render/* (UI and overlays)
```

`GameData` is a single mutable struct passed through update and render.

# Where to put new code

| Concern | Location |
| --- | --- |
| State machine, collisions, waves | `engine.ts` (or future split modules) |
| HUD, menu, overlays, game-over | `render/` |
| Spawn AI, enemy types | `enemies.ts` |
| Weapons, firing patterns | `weapons.ts` |
| Active abilities | `skills.ts` |
| Mode rules, daily modifiers | `modes.ts` |
| Coins, unlocks, achievements | `progress.ts` |
| Tuning numbers | `core/constants.ts` |

# Touch / menu layout

Menu drawing lives in `render/menu.ts`. Layout constants and touch hit testing live in `render/menu-layout.ts` — update both together when menu geometry changes.

# Testing

Add Vitest coverage for new **pure** logic. Rendering and full engine integration are lower priority unless explicitly requested.
